<item>
            <title>[LU-162] CentOS5 cannot load fsfilt_ldiskfs due to unknown symbols used ldiskfs_discard_preallocations</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-162</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After rhel6 patch landed, that&apos;s what you get when trying to use it on centos5 in dmesg:&lt;br/&gt;
ldiskfs created from ext4-2.6-rhel5&lt;br/&gt;
fsfilt_ldiskfs: Unknown symbol ldiskfs_discard_preallocations&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It seems the discard prealloc code checks for the function availability, but not whenever it is exported, so we either need to adjust the heck or add another patch to centos5.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
